        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 3 at 3:55PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 355 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Mancos, or 27 miles west of Durango, moving
southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of south central
Montezuma and west central La Plata Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
